title: Wolverhampton's Oxjam lineup announced
text:
Taking place across six venues and featuring 30 bands and artists, the event is part of a national festival to raise funds for Oxfam. What do you think? Be the first to comment 
The line-up on October 17, includes Shatter Effect, The Assist, Pleasure House, Jump the Shark, Chris Wallbank and the Cowards, Jack Fletcher Band, Ryan Evans, Young Braves, Luke Wylde and the Japes and Viva lanza. 
Venues taking part include the Tap and Ale, the Royal London, the Newhampton Inn, The Grain Store, The Giffard Arms and the Civic Bar, with wristbands available from The Grain Store, Kings Street, from 11.30am on the day. Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
